reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Most satisfying non cloth napkin ever.
reviews.reviewText: I could use these in my bathroom as individual disposable hand towels, and I may still on special occasions. But the real treat is using them at dinnertime. I rarely buy disposable items because I feel it's just wasteful. These are just so perfect. I love how they feel on my skin as well as how absorbent they are. They are fantastic quality and it's nice to have a little luxury every once in a while. Yes, they are disposable. Yes, they are pricey. But boy do I sure enjoy them. I still use cloth napkins most of the time. But when having anything that might permanently stain my cloth, I pull these out. They're also great for the holidays. I justify getting these because I very rarely purchase disposable paper products so might as well get the good stuff. Highly recommend. This package lasts our family of 6 almost 2 years. Have to make sure I never run out.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great all purpose napkins - cloths
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these to used to have a nicer quality cloth for my visitors to wipe their hands on in the bathroom and kitchen. It definitely serves the purpose. They are so large that I actually cut them in half. I use them for napkins at the table, cloths in the bathroom and I can even wipe counters with them because they are very strong. Softness is not awesome but it’s because they’re so strong. Great all purpose cloths. I’ve ordered them twice
